com.sri.ai.util.collect

Class EZIteratorWithNull<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.util.collect.EZIteratorWithNull<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BreadthFirstIterator, FunctionIterator, NestedIterator, PairIterator, ZipIterator

    @Beta
public abstract class EZIteratorWithNull<E>
extends Object
implements Iterator<E>
    An abstract class meant to make the implementation of iterators easier. It is similar to EZIterator, but allows for null elements in the iterator's range. This is accomplished by changing the meaning of calculateNext() returning null. Whereas in EZIterator this was interpreted as the end of the range, here this simply means the next element is null. For calculateNext() to indicate end of range, it calls the new method endOfRange().

    braz
